As the dreaded coronavirus scourge continues to spread across the country, the leadership of the Social Democratic Party (SDP), on Monday, directed all its offices to close down immediately for preventive measures. This was contained in a statement made available to newsmen in Abuja by Amb. Rufus Aiyenigba, the Chief of Staff to the National Chairman of the Party, Prof Tunde Adeniran. ALSO READ: Coronavirus: My son didn’t visit night clubs, Jumat prayer, Atiku cries out The statement indicated that the closure order would be in force till April 14, this year in the first instance. The Party enjoined all members and Nigerians generally to strictly observe the health guidelines, instructions and tips given by the World Health Organisation (WHO) and other relevant agencies. He also appealed to the Federal Government to appreciate the seriousness of the pandemic disease with which Nigeria was currently facing and get all relevant agencies of government to rise up to the challenge which “is now a threat to the survival of every Nigerian.” YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES BREAKING: Atiku Abubakar’s Son Tests Positive For Coronavirus One of the sons of former vice president Atiku Abubakar has tested positive for the novel coronavirus (COVID-19). Atiku who revealed this via his verified Twitter account on Sunday night his son has been transferred to the Gwagwalada Specialist Teaching Hospital in Abuja for the treatment… Read full story Workers’ Salaries In Jeopardy As Oil Price Tumbles Again •FAAC meeting deadlocked as states reject amount presented for sharing AS another economic recession looms in the wake of the global Covid-19 pandemic, there are very present fears among workers of the 36 state governments over the ability of their governments to continue to pay their salaries. On Friday, Brent crude futures fell $1.49 or 5.2%, to settle at $26.98 a barrel. United States… Read full story Northern Youths Begin Sanusi For President Campaign The 2023 presidential campai